  "text": "Detailed conformer studies were carried out for the ketohydroperoxide HPMF (HOOCH 2 OCHO, m/z = 92.011 u) and performic acid [HC(O)OOH, m/z = 62.000 u]. Multiple conformers with non-negligible populations at the temperatures of the sampled beam (∼100 K) were found. We note that the most likely conformers are not necessarily those with the lowest electronic energies, as their relative populations will depend additionally on the local vibrational frequencies and rotational constants. [CITATION_1] Detailed results for the identification of isomers at m/z = 92 u and 62 u are discussed below.",
